ERROR:POINTER_LOCATION: "foo* bar" should be "foo *bar"
#98: FILE: diff.c:574:
+static void show_stats(struct diffstat_t* data, struct diff_options *options)

When using pointer data or a function that returns a pointer type,
the preferred use of * is adjacent to the data name or function name
and not adjacent to the type name.
Examples::

  char *linux_banner;
  unsigned long long memparse(char *ptr, char **retptr);
  char *match_strdup(substring_t *s);

See: https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/process/coding-style.html#spaces

ERROR:ASSIGN_IN_IF: do not use assignment in if condition
#128: FILE: diff.c:603:
+		if (0 < (len = quote_c_style(file->name, NULL, NULL, 0))) {

Do not use assignments in if condition.
Example::

  if ((foo = bar(...)) < BAZ) {

should be written as::

  foo = bar(...);
  if (foo < BAZ) {

WARNING:LINE_SPACING: Missing a blank line after declarations
#130: FILE: diff.c:605:
+			char *qname = xmalloc(len + 1);
+			quote_c_style(file->name, qname, NULL, 0);

Vertical space is wasted given the limited number of lines an
editor window can display when multiple blank lines are used.

See: https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/process/coding-style.html#spaces

WARNING:CONSTANT_COMPARISON: Comparisons should place the constant on the right side of the test
#146: FILE: diff.c:618:
+		if (0 < added && (!min_change || added < min_change))

Comparisons with a constant or upper case identifier on the left
side of the test should be avoided.

WARNING:CONSTANT_COMPARISON: Comparisons should place the constant on the right side of the test
#148: FILE: diff.c:620:
+		if (0 < deleted && (!min_change || deleted < min_change))

ERROR:TRAILING_WHITESPACE: trailing whitespace
#246: FILE: diff.c:689:
+^I^Ishow_name(prefix, name, len, reset, plain);^I^I$

Trailing whitespace should always be removed.
Some editors highlight the trailing whitespace and cause visual
distractions when editing files.

See: https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/process/coding-style.html#spaces

ERROR:ELSE_AFTER_BRACE: else should follow close brace '}'
#271: FILE: diff.c:1742:
+	}
+	else if (!strncmp(arg, "--stat-name-width=", 18)) {

`else {` should follow the closing block `}` on the same line.

See: https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/process/coding-style.html#placing-braces-and-spaces

